1
00:00:52,618 --> 00:00:53,987
Command (Jet): Hunter, do you copy?

2
00:00:53,987 --> 00:00:56,722
Hunter: I'm here, Command, prepping to land on the planet.

3
00:00:57,122 --> 00:00:59,324
Command: Good. Remain on comms till you're needed.

4
00:00:59,325 --> 00:01:02,395
Hunter: Okay. I'll be here. Landing now.

5
00:01:09,968 --> 00:01:12,004
Mono: Hunter, where the fuck are we?

6
00:01:12,171 --> 00:01:15,974
Hunter: Oooo. Language, Mono. We're somewhere out in Backspace.

7
00:01:15,974 --> 00:01:18,710
Mono: What the fuck are we doing out in BackSpace?

8
00:01:19,245 --> 00:01:20,525
Hunter: We're looking for a pod.

9
00:01:21,381 --> 00:01:23,715
Hunter: Go scan for dangerous life forms.

10
00:01:24,817 --> 00:01:25,817
Mono: Scanning

11
00:01:32,659 --> 00:01:35,061
Mono: I really doubt there's anyone out here.

12
00:01:36,763 --> 00:01:37,763
Mono: Scanning

13
00:01:40,266 --> 00:01:41,835
Mono: Still scanning.

14
00:02:02,855 --> 00:02:04,256
Mono: Still scanning.

15
00:02:07,025 --> 00:02:08,594
Mono: Nothing detected.

16
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:23,109
Hunter: Hey, Command, I found the pod, but there's no sign of the crew.

17
00:02:23,643 --> 00:02:25,411
Command: Alright. Stay put.

18
00:02:25,411 --> 00:02:26,445
Command: Don't move.

19
00:02:29,314 --> 00:02:34,120
Falcon 5: I see you, looking for the blackhole, are we?

20
00:02:37,389 --> 00:02:38,733
Hunter: You want me to go look for them?

21
00:02:38,758 --> 00:02:42,395
Command: Just. Please. For once. Do as you're told.

22
00:02:42,762 --> 00:02:43,762
Mono: Scanning.

23
00:02:45,264 --> 00:02:47,566
Mono: Still nothing detected.

24
00:02:52,171 --> 00:02:54,640
Hunter: "Do as you're told..."

25
00:02:54,841 --> 00:02:56,576
Command: We're still on comms.

26
00:02:56,575 --> 00:02:58,144
Command: Everyone can hear you.

27
00:02:58,144 --> 00:03:01,681
Hunter: Right. Listen, Jet, if this is about last night...

28
00:03:01,681 --> 00:03:05,418
Command: Just. Please. We're sending another crew to your location now.

29
00:03:10,956 --> 00:03:12,658
Mono: I've found another ship.

30
00:03:13,926 --> 00:03:15,662
Mono: It appears to be a Falcon.

31
00:03:15,662 --> 00:03:19,699
Hunter: Well, as long as its not a Falcon 5 we're good.

32
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:21,968
Mono: It's a Falcon 5. We're fucked.

33
00:03:21,967 --> 00:03:23,769
Command: Glad to hear somebody is.

34
00:03:23,770 --> 00:03:25,290
Hunter: Whoa... Wait... Wait... Wait... Wait...

35
00:03:27,606 --> 00:03:30,210
[Gunshots]

36
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:32,778
Hunter: It's a Falcon 5! It's a Falcon 5!

37
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:37,049
Hunter: Shit!

38
00:03:54,467 --> 00:04:00,873
Hunter: Shit! (Breathing heavily) I'm outta shape, I'm outta shape.

39
00:04:00,872 --> 00:04:02,574
Let's stop for a second.

40
00:04:07,413 --> 00:04:08,748
Mono: What do we do now?

41
00:04:09,414 --> 00:04:11,216
Hunter: Definitely not staying put!

42
00:04:11,683 --> 00:04:13,186
Let's go find that black hole.

43
00:04:48,588 --> 00:04:51,057
Hunter: I think we found the first crew.

44
00:05:05,237 --> 00:05:06,271
[Gunshot]

45
00:05:10,076 --> 00:05:11,277
Mono: Hunter

46
00:05:12,411 --> 00:05:13,211
Mono: Hunter

47
00:05:13,211 --> 00:05:15,714
Hunter: Stop shooting at me! [Gunshots]

48
00:05:17,216 --> 00:05:20,286
Hunter: Wuhoo-oooo. Mono? You alright?

49
00:05:25,490 --> 00:05:27,726
Hunter: Mono? You okay bud?

50
00:05:27,726 --> 00:05:29,628
Mono: Hunter, where are you?

51
00:05:29,629 --> 00:05:30,730
Hunter: You okay, buddy?

52
00:05:30,730 --> 00:05:32,799
Mono: I can't feel my legs.

53
00:05:32,798 --> 00:05:35,100
Mono: I really wanted to see the blackhole.

54
00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:36,903
Hunter: Hey! You'll be fine.

55
00:05:36,903 --> 00:05:38,471
We'll just reboot you and... -

56
00:05:38,471 --> 00:05:40,572
Mono: Everything's going dark.

57
00:05:42,442 --> 00:05:43,442
Hunter: Come on...

58
00:06:03,262 --> 00:06:05,298
Hunter: I have eyes on the blackhole.

59
00:06:05,298 --> 00:06:07,699
Command: Don't go in. Just stay put.

60
00:06:07,699 --> 00:06:09,468
We'll send a team to check it out.

61
00:06:09,468 --> 00:06:12,504
Hunter: You! You just want me to wait?

62
00:06:12,971 --> 00:06:14,106
Come on!

63
00:06:17,709 --> 00:06:19,378
Command: Do. As. You're. Told.

64
00:06:19,778 --> 00:06:21,279
Stay put.

65
00:06:21,613 --> 00:06:22,781
Hunter: (laughing to himself)

66
00:06:23,014 --> 00:06:23,649
Hunter: No.

67
00:06:23,815 --> 00:06:25,384
Command: What do you mean no?

68
00:06:27,019 --> 00:06:28,454
Hunter: Adventure awaits.

69
00:07:31,884 --> 00:07:33,953
- Mayday! Mayday!

70
00:07:33,952 --> 00:07:37,823
This is Lieutenant Kaya Torres of the DSB Intrepid.

71
00:07:37,824 --> 00:07:41,561
(inaudible panicked yelling)

72
00:08:11,923 --> 00:08:15,293
Mayday. This is Kaya Torres.

73
00:08:16,528 --> 00:08:18,764
I'm a sole survivor of the DSB Intrepid.

74
00:08:20,132 --> 00:08:21,300
Everyone else has gone.

75
00:08:35,248 --> 00:08:40,186
I don't know how I'm getting out of this one mama.

76
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:42,687
Mayday. Mayday. This is Kaya Torres.

77
00:08:42,687 --> 00:08:43,889
Please respond.

78
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:49,762
Mayday. Mayday. This is Lieutenant Kaya Torres.

79
00:08:49,761 --> 00:08:51,463
Please respond.

80
00:08:51,464 --> 00:08:53,966
Cosmic beings, space pirates.

81
00:08:53,966 --> 00:08:56,001
Come on, throw me a bone here.

82
00:08:56,001 --> 00:08:59,104
This is Lieutenant Kaya Torres, please respond.

83
00:08:59,105 --> 00:08:59,938
- [Voice On The Radio] Hello?

84
00:08:59,938 --> 00:09:00,772
- Yes.

85
00:09:00,773 --> 00:09:01,606
- Hello? - Yes,

86
00:09:01,606 --> 00:09:02,440
- Can you hear?

87
00:09:02,441 --> 00:09:04,043
- Yes! Yes!

88
00:09:04,043 --> 00:09:07,013
Why's the fucking signal so-fucking gravity.

89
00:09:16,154 --> 00:09:17,155
Survey says,

90
00:09:18,658 --> 00:09:21,427
3543% increase.

91
00:09:22,595 --> 00:09:23,863
Yeah. That should work.

92
00:09:33,038 --> 00:09:34,173
Hello stranger.

93
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:38,177
My name is Kaya Torres.

94
00:09:38,177 --> 00:09:39,912
I'm marooned on my life pod.

95
00:09:41,746 --> 00:09:43,214
I have a busted ship

96
00:09:43,215 --> 00:09:46,085
and I am circling a black hole against my will.

97
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:47,086
Please send help.

98
00:10:07,005 --> 00:10:08,006
- Kaya Torres

99
00:10:08,941 --> 00:10:11,310
Oh, a real actual person

100
00:10:11,309 --> 00:10:14,012
wish I could say I'm sending a rescue crew but...

101
00:10:14,013 --> 00:10:15,681
I'm in the same situation you are,

102
00:10:16,849 --> 00:10:19,085
not circling black hole though.

103
00:10:19,085 --> 00:10:20,820
Did you take a wrong turn?

104
00:10:20,820 --> 00:10:22,321
Navigation didn't have the latest,

105
00:10:22,321 --> 00:10:25,423
here's a black hole you shouldn't fly here update?

106
00:10:25,423 --> 00:10:26,424
- Funny.

107
00:10:27,927 --> 00:10:29,528
- Honestly I'm surprised you reached me at all,

108
00:10:29,528 --> 00:10:30,830
the atmosphere here.

109
00:10:30,830 --> 00:10:33,399
Oh, did I mention I'm on a planet?

110
00:10:34,332 --> 00:10:35,800
I'm a cartographer.

111
00:10:35,801 --> 00:10:38,371
I make maps for a living I did until I crashed on a rock

112
00:10:38,370 --> 00:10:40,939
so massive it wouldn't let me back out.

113
00:10:40,940 --> 00:10:42,274
Gravity,

114
00:10:42,274 --> 00:10:43,274
always fun.

115
00:10:44,476 --> 00:10:46,312
I've been trying to initiate a proper call link

116
00:10:46,312 --> 00:10:47,846
between your gravity problems and mine

117
00:10:47,846 --> 00:10:50,949
we have a serious time displacement going on,

118
00:10:50,950 --> 00:10:52,652
Kaya Torres from the doomed Intrepid

119
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:54,920
If you want an interstellar pen pal,

120
00:10:54,919 --> 00:10:57,088
feel free to drop me a line.

121
00:10:57,089 --> 00:10:58,724
No one should be alone out there.

122
00:11:03,361 --> 00:11:04,697
- So what do I call you?

123
00:11:06,065 --> 00:11:07,066
Map boy?

124
00:11:09,168 --> 00:11:11,736
I've been busy fighting physics.

125
00:11:13,038 --> 00:11:15,908
This pod has just enough juice to keep me from,

126
00:11:15,908 --> 00:11:17,375
getting swallowed up.

127
00:11:20,111 --> 00:11:21,546
But if I modify the power flow

128
00:11:21,547 --> 00:11:24,550
I think I can punch my way out of the well,

129
00:11:26,619 --> 00:11:27,820
that's the idea anyway.

130
00:11:31,123 --> 00:11:32,958
You don't realize how quiet space can be

131
00:11:32,957 --> 00:11:34,360
until you're drifting in it.

132
00:11:36,162 --> 00:11:38,129
I thought I'd be okay but fuck

133
00:11:39,831 --> 00:11:41,766
I could really use a pen pal right now.

134
00:11:52,278 --> 00:11:53,345
- You're still there.

135
00:11:54,513 --> 00:11:56,615
I wasn't expecting to hear from you again.

136
00:11:56,615 --> 00:11:58,850
Hammer. My name is Hammer

137
00:11:58,850 --> 00:12:00,452
- Hammer?

138
00:12:00,452 --> 00:12:03,855
- Yes. That's my real actual name.

139
00:12:05,291 --> 00:12:08,060
I think my father wanted me to be a blacksmith or a lawman.

140
00:12:08,961 --> 00:12:10,462
Definitely not a cartographer.

141
00:12:12,230 --> 00:12:13,732
You hear that?

142
00:12:13,732 --> 00:12:15,700
It's a massive sand storm going on outside my cave

143
00:12:16,601 --> 00:12:18,471
planet has them constantly.

144
00:12:18,471 --> 00:12:20,605
You'd die if you stood in the middle of one,

145
00:12:22,073 --> 00:12:24,676
they scare me. Every time.

146
00:12:26,678 --> 00:12:29,280
is fuck a curse word?

147
00:12:30,582 --> 00:12:31,583
Fuck.

148
00:12:35,153 --> 00:12:36,322
A little click at end.

149
00:12:36,322 --> 00:12:37,322
Lovely.

150
00:12:40,860 --> 00:12:43,962
- How have you never heard the glory which is the F word?

151
00:12:43,962 --> 00:12:45,563
It's fucking timeless.

152
00:12:46,398 --> 00:12:47,867
Also why cartography?

153
00:12:47,866 --> 00:12:50,702
Was it to get back to your parents for naming you Hammer?

154
00:12:51,971 --> 00:12:53,371
- I wanted to explore.

155
00:12:53,371 --> 00:12:55,306
find places no one had ever seen be remembered

156
00:12:55,307 --> 00:12:56,642
for something when I'm gone.

157
00:12:57,809 --> 00:12:59,043
Wow. That sounds really egotistical

158
00:12:59,043 --> 00:13:00,612
when you say it out loud, doesn't it?

159
00:13:02,748 --> 00:13:03,749
What do you do Kaya?

160
00:13:04,884 --> 00:13:06,384
What's your passion?

161
00:13:06,384 --> 00:13:07,418
I'm an engineer.

162
00:13:09,721 --> 00:13:11,122
I tinker. I,

163
00:13:12,258 --> 00:13:13,259
fix things.

164
00:13:16,729 --> 00:13:17,863
When you're a mechanic,

165
00:13:19,164 --> 00:13:20,865
you're constantly solving puzzles.

166
00:13:23,903 --> 00:13:26,004
Space has the best puzzles.

167
00:13:28,606 --> 00:13:30,241
- I've cooked this local abomination

168
00:13:30,241 --> 00:13:32,310
of a vegetable 46 different ways.

169
00:13:33,345 --> 00:13:35,247
Crispy, steamed,

170
00:13:35,246 --> 00:13:37,817
fried, it doesn't matter. It's always disgusting.

171
00:13:40,485 --> 00:13:41,953
At least you don't have to suffer through

172
00:13:41,953 --> 00:13:45,024
pre-process rations and nutritional pills every day.

173
00:13:46,125 --> 00:13:47,692
I'm eating a fucking mystery meat.

174
00:13:50,428 --> 00:13:51,629
God, I miss meat.

175
00:13:54,066 --> 00:13:56,201
Here's a list of foods I wish I was eating,

176
00:13:58,070 --> 00:13:59,605
a block of cheddar cheese,

177
00:14:01,874 --> 00:14:02,875
and avocado,

178
00:14:05,277 --> 00:14:06,545
actually just an avocado.

179
00:14:11,049 --> 00:14:12,250
- Nah they're long gone.

180
00:14:13,118 --> 00:14:14,119
Yours?

181
00:14:18,524 --> 00:14:19,892
- Used to be me and my mom.

182
00:14:21,259 --> 00:14:23,062
She was a master mechanic,

183
00:14:24,062 --> 00:14:25,931
lover of puzzles,

184
00:14:25,931 --> 00:14:27,199
all around firecracker.

185
00:14:28,267 --> 00:14:29,668
Taught me everything I know.

186
00:14:32,370 --> 00:14:34,240
a few years ago she got methyl rash.

187
00:14:36,575 --> 00:14:37,710
You're prone to it when you work in

188
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:39,311
the belly of a ship long enough.

189
00:14:44,549 --> 00:14:46,851
Then the lining in your lungs breaks down and,

190
00:14:51,990 --> 00:14:54,025
it's shitty how frail we are.

191
00:15:00,466 --> 00:15:02,067
What's your biggest fear Hammer?

192
00:15:03,369 --> 00:15:04,870
you can trust me I won't tell.

193
00:15:10,208 --> 00:15:11,209
- To be forgotten.

194
00:15:13,711 --> 00:15:14,712
What's yours?

195
00:15:18,650 --> 00:15:19,651
- To die alone.

196
00:15:40,438 --> 00:15:42,006
No!

197
00:15:42,006 --> 00:15:43,508
No no no no no no.

198
00:15:46,378 --> 00:15:47,379
Ahh!

199
00:16:02,327 --> 00:16:05,163
It put me even closer than before.

200
00:16:08,701 --> 00:16:11,403
Trying to conserve resources as much as I can.

201
00:16:13,304 --> 00:16:14,305
I'm losing ground.

202
00:16:15,506 --> 00:16:16,507
Bit by bit.

203
00:16:19,577 --> 00:16:20,946
Maybe I should stop trying.

204
00:16:22,815 --> 00:16:23,816
One final adventure.

205
00:16:29,053 --> 00:16:30,688
There are worse ways to go right?

206
00:16:35,461 --> 00:16:36,595
I'm so scared Hammer.

207
00:16:42,835 --> 00:16:43,836
- Hey,

208
00:16:44,903 --> 00:16:46,071
don't give up.

209
00:16:48,006 --> 00:16:49,774
I'm not going anywhere.

210
00:16:50,842 --> 00:16:52,443
I'll keep my line open okay?

211
00:16:55,313 --> 00:16:56,615
One of us needs to escape.

212
00:17:02,587 --> 00:17:03,588
- Hey,

213
00:17:04,423 --> 00:17:05,790
can I get a picture of you?

214
00:17:08,493 --> 00:17:10,228
I want to put a face to this voice.

215
00:17:56,875 --> 00:17:58,544
- Words don't do you justice Kaya.

216
00:18:05,784 --> 00:18:07,052
- Guess what I'm drinking?

217
00:18:12,723 --> 00:18:13,724
Vodka.

218
00:18:16,327 --> 00:18:17,930
It's supposed to be for cleaning.

219
00:18:19,198 --> 00:18:20,566
I have a confession.

220
00:18:23,769 --> 00:18:27,239
I have been thinking about you.

221
00:18:27,239 --> 00:18:31,076
And I kind of wish

222
00:18:31,076 --> 00:18:33,979
I was on that planet right now.

223
00:18:39,585 --> 00:18:41,987
I don't know what vodka is, but I like the mood

224
00:18:41,987 --> 00:18:43,188
it's putting you in.

225
00:18:43,188 --> 00:18:45,424
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait, hold on. Wait.

226
00:18:46,424 --> 00:18:48,192
You don't know what vodka is?

227
00:18:48,192 --> 00:18:49,193
How?

228
00:18:50,528 --> 00:18:52,830
I'm beginning to wonder if you're real at all.

229
00:18:53,664 --> 00:18:54,665
Explain sir,

230
00:18:55,968 --> 00:18:58,170
- is my sheltered upbringing showing? Figures.

231
00:18:58,170 --> 00:19:00,439
This is what I get for being raised on Tremamine.

232
00:19:00,439 --> 00:19:01,974
- Tremamine

233
00:19:01,973 --> 00:19:03,575
- I suppose you're going to tell me I wouldn't be fit for,

234
00:19:03,575 --> 00:19:05,009
- Tremamine

235
00:19:05,009 --> 00:19:06,010
- coupling either?

236
00:19:07,378 --> 00:19:10,081
Let it be known, I am fully knowledgeable in,

237
00:19:11,083 --> 00:19:12,084
such things,

238
00:19:12,851 --> 00:19:13,852
if you were here.

239
00:19:16,721 --> 00:19:19,357
- Timeout, I've never heard of Tremamine,

240
00:19:19,357 --> 00:19:21,326
is it near Titan?

241
00:19:21,326 --> 00:19:22,361
Jupiter?

242
00:19:24,596 --> 00:19:26,265
Is it one of those weird Jupiter moons?

243
00:19:26,265 --> 00:19:27,299
No one talks about?

244
00:19:28,599 --> 00:19:29,600
- Jupiter?

245
00:19:30,669 --> 00:19:31,670
Titan?

246
00:19:32,904 --> 00:19:35,874
Kaya, I've memorized every colonized system.

247
00:19:37,041 --> 00:19:38,476
I've never heard of those planets.

248
00:19:39,611 --> 00:19:40,646
How is that possible?

249
00:19:45,851 --> 00:19:46,985
- No fucking way.

250
00:19:49,922 --> 00:19:52,324
- Hammer I'm sending you an energy signature.

251
00:19:52,324 --> 00:19:54,526
Do a scan on your end tell me what you find.

252
00:19:55,594 --> 00:19:57,895
- Fuck. I found it,

253
00:19:57,895 --> 00:20:00,264
but the signal's reversed.

254
00:20:01,833 --> 00:20:03,535
What does that mean?

255
00:20:03,535 --> 00:20:04,836
- It's the little stuff.

256
00:20:06,104 --> 00:20:08,874
It's the different curse words.

257
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:10,909
It's the different planets.

258
00:20:10,909 --> 00:20:12,477
The alcohol,

259
00:20:12,477 --> 00:20:15,514
your messages come in at the same delay every time.

260
00:20:15,513 --> 00:20:16,814
What if you heard my broadcast

261
00:20:16,815 --> 00:20:18,383
because it's not a black hole at all?

262
00:20:18,383 --> 00:20:19,484
I mean shit What if it-

263
00:20:19,483 --> 00:20:21,452
What if it's a wormhole?

264
00:20:21,452 --> 00:20:25,590
But not to another spot in the galaxy, it's um,

265
00:20:25,590 --> 00:20:26,724
to another universe, Hammer.

266
00:20:26,724 --> 00:20:28,392
You're in an alternate universe.

267
00:20:29,595 --> 00:20:31,063
And I think I can get to you.

268
00:20:32,431 --> 00:20:34,600
Slow down, remember gravity.

269
00:20:34,599 --> 00:20:36,534
Even if what you're orbiting isn't a black hole,

270
00:20:36,535 --> 00:20:38,570
you can be crushed just by crossing over.

271
00:20:38,569 --> 00:20:41,973
I can't fix my bucket of a ship without your help Kaya.

272
00:20:41,973 --> 00:20:44,742
Don't plow into the unknown on a hunch.

273
00:20:44,742 --> 00:20:46,043
Don't leave me.

274
00:20:48,279 --> 00:20:49,748
- There's nothing left the other way.

275
00:20:49,748 --> 00:20:51,250
Not anymore.

276
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:54,219
If I burn full throttle, I can make it to your planet.

277
00:20:54,219 --> 00:20:56,054
Someone's got to save your sorry ass.

278
00:20:57,722 --> 00:20:59,691
We're going to escape together.

279
00:20:59,691 --> 00:21:01,727
That's how we solve this puzzle.

280
00:21:01,727 --> 00:21:03,461
Hang on hammer. I'll see you soon.

281
00:21:27,385 --> 00:21:31,056
(multiple voices screaming)

282
00:21:42,401 --> 00:21:44,169
- No one should be alone out there.

283
00:22:53,171 --> 00:22:54,172
Hello Kaya.

284
00:22:56,842 --> 00:22:58,410
If you're watching this,

285
00:22:58,410 --> 00:22:59,878
it means you finally made it.

286
00:23:01,413 --> 00:23:02,413
I'm glad you did.

287
00:23:03,914 --> 00:23:05,649
You're probably confused right now.

288
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:10,255
If you want to know the answer,

289
00:23:13,357 --> 00:23:14,358
its gravity.

290
00:23:16,127 --> 00:23:17,294
Your favorite subject.

291
00:23:18,396 --> 00:23:20,030
You traveled through the wormhole,

292
00:23:22,233 --> 00:23:24,769
time on your end has slowed down,

293
00:23:26,872 --> 00:23:28,539
what you experienced in days.

294
00:23:33,811 --> 00:23:37,415
In the meantime, I tried my best.

295
00:23:39,483 --> 00:23:40,484
I did.

296
00:23:42,887 --> 00:23:44,622
There's a storm coming in and,

297
00:23:49,326 --> 00:23:51,829
I think I wanna go for a walk.

298
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:56,535
There's worse ways to go huh?

299
00:24:00,704 --> 00:24:02,406
I waited as long as I could Kaya.

300
00:24:05,410 --> 00:24:06,411
I'm so tired.

301
00:24:09,146 --> 00:24:11,549
I left some recordings for you on this terminal.

302
00:24:14,719 --> 00:24:16,587
At least one a day. Every day.

303
00:24:18,923 --> 00:24:23,561
And hopefully it'll keep you from being so lonely.

304
00:24:25,130 --> 00:24:26,364
If you fix my ship,

305
00:24:27,365 --> 00:24:28,967
and you get off this rock,

306
00:24:30,535 --> 00:24:31,636
don't forget about me.

307
00:24:34,506 --> 00:24:35,774
I never forgot about you.

308
00:25:05,069 --> 00:25:06,504
- Hello, new universe.

309
00:25:12,243 --> 00:25:14,211
My name is Kaya Torres.

310
00:25:15,779 --> 00:25:18,148
I'm trapped on a planet in the middle of fucking nowhere.

311
00:25:18,148 --> 00:25:19,316
I have two busted ships,

312
00:25:19,317 --> 00:25:21,853
and my odds of escaping are terrible.

313
00:25:23,922 --> 00:25:25,423
But I'm alive.

314
00:25:25,423 --> 00:25:28,259
So if you need someone to talk to drop me a line.

315
00:25:35,634 --> 00:25:37,301
No one should be alone out there.

316
00:27:05,700 --> 00:27:09,938
[MUSIC PLAYING]

317
00:27:19,580 --> 00:27:20,580
Mavis?

318
00:27:21,347 --> 00:27:22,649
Hello, Kainoa.

319
00:27:22,650 --> 00:27:24,653
I'm not getting a reading from your transport.

320
00:27:24,952 --> 00:27:25,820
No shit.

321
00:27:25,820 --> 00:27:26,821
It's totaled.

322
00:27:27,056 --> 00:27:27,690
That's strange.

323
00:27:27,690 --> 00:27:29,292
We just did maintenance on it.

324
00:27:29,291 --> 00:27:30,426
I'll run diagnostics.

325
00:27:30,961 --> 00:27:32,062
How's comms really doing?

326
00:27:32,695 --> 00:27:33,363
Still down.

327
00:27:33,364 --> 00:27:34,531
I'm afraid we're on our own.

328
00:27:35,365 --> 00:27:36,634
Give me my distance from home.

329
00:27:37,403 --> 00:27:40,173
Base 5 is 9.76 kilometers southwest

330
00:27:40,173 --> 00:27:41,208
of your current position.

331
00:27:42,041 --> 00:27:43,042
OK, plot a route for me.

332
00:27:43,911 --> 00:27:46,080
Gravitational waves are currently in sector 10

333
00:27:46,079 --> 00:27:48,549
and moving northwest at three kilometers per hour.

334
00:27:48,549 --> 00:27:49,684
You should be in the clear.

335
00:27:50,086 --> 00:27:50,586
Good.

336
00:27:50,586 --> 00:27:51,887
Keep me updated.

337
00:27:51,887 --> 00:27:54,858
And Mavis, prepare a fresh O2 canister for me, yeah?

338
00:27:55,358 --> 00:27:56,460
Copy that.

339
00:27:56,460 --> 00:27:58,096
You need to move now.

340
00:27:58,096 --> 00:28:00,365
You have just enough to get back to base.

341
00:28:00,365 --> 00:28:01,867
Tonight is the night.

342
00:28:18,055 --> 00:28:19,157
Uncle, what are you doing?

343
00:28:21,192 --> 00:28:22,192
What are you doing?

344
00:28:22,528 --> 00:28:25,932
Mom told me to find you.

345
00:28:25,932 --> 00:28:27,201
Is that where you're going?

346
00:28:29,670 --> 00:28:31,473
You see those two stars right there?

347
00:28:32,406 --> 00:28:33,407
Those two?

348
00:28:33,643 --> 00:28:36,144
Yeah.

349
00:28:36,144 --> 00:28:41,952
But take your thumb like that, and line it up with the stars.

350
00:28:41,952 --> 00:28:45,156
And that spot right above your hand--

351
00:28:45,156 --> 00:28:46,291
that's where Uncle's going.

352
00:28:48,295 --> 00:28:50,664
I don't see anything.

353
00:28:50,664 --> 00:28:51,664
What's that star?

354
00:28:52,866 --> 00:28:54,869
Oh, that one?

355
00:28:54,869 --> 00:28:57,406
Maybe you'll go there someday.

356
00:28:57,406 --> 00:29:00,076
Come on.

357
00:29:00,076 --> 00:29:01,478
How's [INAUDIBLE] tonight?

358
00:29:02,145 --> 00:29:03,080
The same.

359
00:29:03,080 --> 00:29:05,216
He's a bit happier since Dad showed up.

360
00:29:05,951 --> 00:29:07,720
Of course, he is.

361
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:11,525
[CHATTER AND LAUGHING]

362
00:29:14,362 --> 00:29:15,362
Keala.

363
00:29:15,762 --> 00:29:16,263
Yes.

364
00:29:16,565 --> 00:29:17,232
Do we have beer?

365
00:29:17,398 --> 00:29:18,166
Yeah, I know.

366
00:29:18,299 --> 00:29:19,299
Oh, hi.

367
00:29:20,237 --> 00:29:21,271
Good luck out there, OK?

368
00:29:21,270 --> 00:29:22,571
We're really going to miss you.

369
00:29:23,374 --> 00:29:24,374
Thanks.

370
00:29:24,976 --> 00:29:26,210
Take care of yourself, OK?

371
00:29:26,444 --> 00:29:27,444
OK.

372
00:29:29,413 --> 00:29:30,717
We're really going to miss you.

373
00:29:31,250 --> 00:29:32,818
Sure.

374
00:29:32,818 --> 00:29:34,421
She hasn't let up since grade school.

375
00:29:34,654 --> 00:29:37,024
Yeah, there's nothing she wants to be under that rainbow.

376
00:29:43,799 --> 00:29:46,370
He hasn't been the same since Mom passed.

377
00:29:46,371 --> 00:29:47,371
He needed you here.

378
00:29:48,105 --> 00:29:49,173
We've been over this.

379
00:29:49,173 --> 00:29:50,843
It wasn't possible.

380
00:29:50,843 --> 00:29:52,510
Honestly, it wasn't my decision to make.

381
00:29:58,586 --> 00:30:00,288
Hey, enough excuses.

382
00:30:00,288 --> 00:30:01,288
Fix it.

383
00:30:06,497 --> 00:30:10,035
Just a reminder-- the last downed peg is near the base.

384
00:30:10,035 --> 00:30:13,239
Atlas Major sets in less than six hours.

385
00:30:13,239 --> 00:30:14,740
We need the system up before then.

386
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:15,840
I know.

387
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:16,342
I know.

388
00:30:16,343 --> 00:30:17,510
Or we miss our window.

389
00:30:18,244 --> 00:30:18,978
Oh, that's right.

390
00:30:18,979 --> 00:30:19,747
I forgot.

391
00:30:19,747 --> 00:30:21,449
You know everything.

392
00:30:21,449 --> 00:30:22,817
Not liking that tone.

393
00:30:23,685 --> 00:30:26,087
Your internal settings need to be turned down.

394
00:30:27,089 --> 00:30:28,891
Hm, sounds like a personal issue.

395
00:30:29,527 --> 00:30:30,561
[SNICKERS]

396
00:30:31,061 --> 00:30:33,664
By the way, I tried to review the transport maintenance logs,

397
00:30:33,664 --> 00:30:34,499
but I'm blocked out.

398
00:30:34,499 --> 00:30:35,499
It's scrambled.

399
00:30:35,967 --> 00:30:37,836
That doesn't make any sense.

400
00:30:37,836 --> 00:30:39,305
First the pegs.

401
00:30:39,305 --> 00:30:40,306
Now this?

402
00:30:40,606 --> 00:30:41,741
Something's not adding up.

403
00:30:41,741 --> 00:30:42,741
I'll keep trying.

404
00:30:43,411 --> 00:30:45,246
Look, let's just get through tonight.

405
00:30:45,246 --> 00:30:46,247
How much further?

406
00:30:46,548 --> 00:30:47,650
You're close.

407
00:30:47,650 --> 00:30:49,317
You'll have a visual of home base

408
00:30:49,317 --> 00:30:51,153
and the pit just over this hill.

409
00:30:53,090 --> 00:30:55,058
That's what we're calling it?

410
00:30:55,058 --> 00:30:55,559
[CHATTER]

411
00:30:55,727 --> 00:30:56,595
Excuse me, everybody.

412
00:30:56,595 --> 00:30:59,097
Can we gather around really quick?

413
00:30:59,097 --> 00:31:02,970
Um, we're just going to-- no, no, no, no.

414
00:31:02,970 --> 00:31:04,538
Where do you think you're going?

415
00:31:04,538 --> 00:31:07,976
We're going to toast Kainoa before he leaves this.

416
00:31:07,976 --> 00:31:12,181
Kainoa, ever since we were kids, I always

417
00:31:12,181 --> 00:31:14,684
knew you were destined to do great things.

418
00:31:14,684 --> 00:31:17,388
And we are incredibly proud to be proud of you.

419
00:31:19,959 --> 00:31:24,663
Mom would be proud, and I'm trying not to think

420
00:31:24,663 --> 00:31:27,134
of this as a going away party.

421
00:31:27,134 --> 00:31:30,939
15 years is a long time for someone to be gone,

422
00:31:30,939 --> 00:31:32,074
but you've worked so hard.

423
00:31:37,181 --> 00:31:45,182
To your journey out there and your safe return home.

424
00:31:45,625 --> 00:31:46,960
I love you, baby brother.

425
00:31:47,961 --> 00:31:48,961
I love you.

426
00:31:48,996 --> 00:31:49,697
To Kainoa.

427
00:31:49,696 --> 00:31:50,696
(ALL) To Kainoa.

428
00:31:53,536 --> 00:31:55,638
Dad?

429
00:31:55,637 --> 00:31:57,072
Maybe you want to say a few words.

430
00:32:07,886 --> 00:32:10,790
Warning-- rogue gravitational wave detected.

431
00:32:10,790 --> 00:32:14,028
Brace yourself.

432
00:32:14,028 --> 00:32:17,834
[THUMPING]

433
00:32:19,403 --> 00:32:24,174
I would like to say a few words.

434
00:32:24,174 --> 00:32:26,377
Hey.

435
00:32:26,377 --> 00:32:29,316
When I became a member of this family,

436
00:32:29,316 --> 00:32:34,087
I'd been so stoked to say that my brother is an astronaut.

437
00:32:34,087 --> 00:32:35,990
And [INAUDIBLE].

438
00:32:35,990 --> 00:32:39,461
[GRUNTS AND ROCKS CRUMBLING]

439
00:32:39,461 --> 00:32:43,901
[MUFFLED VOICE]

440
00:32:44,401 --> 00:32:49,342
[BEEPING]

441
00:32:53,980 --> 00:32:54,714
Was that OK?

442
00:32:54,714 --> 00:32:55,750
[INAUDIBLE]

443
00:32:55,750 --> 00:32:57,050
I didn't know what else to say.

444
00:32:57,050 --> 00:32:57,985
No, that was good.

445
00:32:57,986 --> 00:32:59,021
Thank you so much.

446
00:32:59,020 --> 00:33:00,021
Can you go check on Dad?

447
00:33:00,021 --> 00:33:02,258
I'll check on Kainoa.

448
00:33:02,258 --> 00:33:03,259
[BEEPING]

449
00:33:03,326 --> 00:33:05,261
Your O2 levels are dropping fast.

450
00:33:05,261 --> 00:33:06,998
There's a leak in your intake hose.

451
00:33:06,998 --> 00:33:09,134
You need to patch it immediately.

452
00:33:09,134 --> 00:33:11,970
You know where the emergency sealant is.

453
00:33:11,970 --> 00:33:13,472
Hello?

454
00:33:13,472 --> 00:33:14,472
Come in.

455
00:33:14,840 --> 00:33:15,875
Copy.

456
00:33:15,875 --> 00:33:18,645
I'm here.

457
00:33:18,645 --> 00:33:20,581
Do I have enough to make it back?

458
00:33:21,082 --> 00:33:22,718
Your CO2 levels are critical.

459
00:33:23,451 --> 00:33:25,655
But I can still make it back.

460
00:33:25,655 --> 00:33:26,757
There's enough time.

461
00:33:26,757 --> 00:33:28,191
There has to be something I can do.

462
00:33:29,426 --> 00:33:31,695
I'm so sorry, Kainoa.

463
00:33:34,465 --> 00:33:37,503
[SCREAMS]

464
00:33:38,003 --> 00:33:44,879
Kainoa, he's not entirely wrong, you know.

465
00:33:48,017 --> 00:33:52,022
What if something happens while you're out there?

466
00:33:52,021 --> 00:33:53,657
What if he's gone before you come back?

467
00:33:53,791 --> 00:33:54,725
Why would he care?

468
00:33:54,726 --> 00:33:55,861
Huh?

469
00:33:55,861 --> 00:33:56,362
Why?

470
00:33:56,862 --> 00:33:59,266
[INTERPOSING VOICES]

471
00:33:59,732 --> 00:34:00,732
It's stupid.

472
00:34:06,008 --> 00:34:07,009
You weren't here.

473
00:34:12,349 --> 00:34:15,251
I was.

474
00:34:15,251 --> 00:34:19,625
While you were at training, I watched cancer take Mom.

475
00:34:19,626 --> 00:34:23,097
And when Dad fell apart, everything [INAUDIBLE] me.

476
00:34:27,001 --> 00:34:31,407
You need to make this right.

477
00:34:31,407 --> 00:34:34,945
Tonight is your last chance.

478
00:34:34,945 --> 00:34:37,448
And you are going to regret this if you don't.

479
00:34:40,918 --> 00:34:41,918
Kainoa.

480
00:35:23,375 --> 00:35:25,545
Kainoa, you're too far out.

481
00:35:26,746 --> 00:35:27,980
OK.

482
00:35:27,980 --> 00:35:28,981
OK.

483
00:35:33,353 --> 00:35:35,323
I'm going to finish this.

484
00:35:46,704 --> 00:35:47,773
What did Grandma do?

485
00:35:49,309 --> 00:35:50,477
She was a geologist.

486
00:35:52,545 --> 00:35:53,947
Isn't that what Uncle Kainoa does?

487
00:35:55,751 --> 00:35:58,186
Yes.

488
00:35:58,186 --> 00:36:01,490
Geologists help us to learn more about the Earth--

489
00:36:01,490 --> 00:36:05,597
what it's made of, how it's formed.

490
00:36:05,597 --> 00:36:09,068
He wanted to be one, just like your grandmother.

491
00:36:10,702 --> 00:36:12,172
Is that why he's flying up there?

492
00:36:20,114 --> 00:36:22,384
Why are you so mad at him?

493
00:36:22,385 --> 00:36:24,120
Didn't Grandma want him to go?

494
00:36:26,023 --> 00:36:27,658
Jada?

495
00:36:27,657 --> 00:36:28,659
Hey, Mom wants you.

496
00:36:50,554 --> 00:36:52,957
I'm not trying to abandon the family.

497
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:03,438
There's nothing that's going to keep me from going, Dad.

498
00:37:06,541 --> 00:37:09,947
But no matter what, I'm still your son.

499
00:37:09,947 --> 00:37:12,817
I'm sorry that I wasn't here when Mom died.

500
00:37:19,259 --> 00:37:20,460
I wasn't here to say goodbye.

501
00:37:25,733 --> 00:37:28,704
I just wanted you to know that before I leave.

502
00:37:38,516 --> 00:37:39,516
Kainoa.

503
00:37:47,695 --> 00:37:49,999
I never wanted you to be anyone but yourself.

504
00:37:52,802 --> 00:37:58,744
I just lost your mother.

505
00:38:02,215 --> 00:38:05,318
I'm not ready to lose my son, too.

506
00:38:09,757 --> 00:38:10,757
Dad?

507
00:38:25,144 --> 00:38:26,913
We have a successful chain reaction

508
00:38:26,913 --> 00:38:31,018
within the peg matrix and topographical and subterranean

509
00:38:31,018 --> 00:38:32,920
data coming in clear.

510
00:38:32,920 --> 00:38:37,225
Connection with Atlas Major established.

511
00:38:37,226 --> 00:38:38,227
You did it.

512
00:38:39,295 --> 00:38:43,167
Initiate corporate correspondence transmission.

513
00:38:43,168 --> 00:38:48,141
Kainoa Kalewa, chief geoengineer of base 5.

514
00:38:48,141 --> 00:38:51,945
I'm stranded near Sector 1 with a depleted oxygen canister

515
00:38:51,945 --> 00:38:53,648
and suit breach.

516
00:38:53,648 --> 00:38:56,352
I am unable to make it back to base 5

517
00:38:56,351 --> 00:38:59,288
after transport malfunction.

518
00:38:59,289 --> 00:39:03,594
Unable to determine cause due to data corruption.

519
00:39:03,594 --> 00:39:04,862
Requesting internal review.

520
00:39:04,862 --> 00:39:05,862
Over.

521
00:39:06,797 --> 00:39:09,534
I still don't know what caused the energy pack to blow.

522
00:39:09,534 --> 00:39:12,239
Everything in the data logs is blocking me out.

523
00:39:12,239 --> 00:39:13,239
Shall I keep trying?

524
00:39:13,639 --> 00:39:14,875
No, Mavis.

525
00:39:14,876 --> 00:39:16,378
Just file it with corporate.

526
00:39:18,047 --> 00:39:20,682
You know, if I had a physical body,

527
00:39:20,682 --> 00:39:23,420
I'd come out there and carry you back to base myself.

528
00:39:25,356 --> 00:39:26,958
Thanks, Mavis.

529
00:39:26,958 --> 00:39:28,260
I appreciate that.

530
00:39:31,297 --> 00:39:32,297
Mavis?

531
00:39:32,798 --> 00:39:33,798
Hm?

532
00:39:34,233 --> 00:39:37,404
Could you record one last transmission for me?

533
00:39:37,405 --> 00:39:38,406
Personal.

534
00:39:39,541 --> 00:39:42,077
It would be an honor.

535
00:39:42,077 --> 00:39:44,079
Initiating correspondence.

536
00:39:47,117 --> 00:39:48,253
I am Kainoa Kalewa.

537
00:39:52,391 --> 00:39:56,730
My sister is Keala Morris.

538
00:39:56,730 --> 00:40:02,704
Her husband, my brother-in-law, is Jacob Morris.

539
00:40:02,704 --> 00:40:06,242
My niece is Jada Morris.

540
00:40:09,646 --> 00:40:16,456
My mother is Jada Kalewa.

541
00:40:16,456 --> 00:40:21,930
And my dad is David Kalewa.

542
00:40:27,670 --> 00:40:29,572
Tell them I said I love them.

543
00:40:34,413 --> 00:40:36,815
Tell them I said goodbye.

544
00:40:42,088 --> 00:40:43,389
We did it, Dad.

545
00:40:49,565 --> 00:40:50,565
Over.

546
00:40:53,070 --> 00:40:55,974
MAVIS: Relaying transmission now.

547
00:41:15,932 --> 00:41:18,170
Transmission received.

548
00:42:01,518 --> 00:42:09,518
♪

549
